      "Can I get a divorce for under $5,000 in Jacksonville?",
      "Yes, if you and your spouse agree on all terms. An uncontested divorce flat fee of $2,000 to $3,000 in attorney fees plus the $414 court filing fee comes to a total of $2,414 to $3,414. This is well under $5,000. You must have a signed marital settlement agreement dividing your assets and debts, and both parties must agree on all issues before filing.",
      "Ready to Schedule Your Jacksonville Divorce Consultation?",
      "Delaying your legal decisions can quickly drive up court fees and stretch out emotional stress. Choosing the right path for your case starts with knowing exactly what you will pay ahead of time. For an uncontested divorce, the cost of divorce Jacksonville Florida couples pay ranges from $2,414 to $3,414 total, giving you a predictable path forward. If your situation is more complex, understanding the full range of options helps you protect your family and your finances.",
      "Ready to move forward with your case? Schedule Your Consultation with an experienced Jacksonville family law attorney today.",
